00037 MTKt_status MtkFileType(
00038   const char *filename,    
00039   MTKt_FileType *filetype   )
00040 {
00041   MTKt_status status;
00042   MTKt_status status_code;
00043   intn hdf_status;
00044   int32 Fid = FAIL;
00045   #ifdef _WIN32 /* Work around so Visual C++ 2005 will compile correctly with /O2 */
00046     char temp_filename[1000];
00047   #endif
00048   
00049   if (filename == NULL)
00050     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_NULLPTR);
00051 
00052   #ifdef _WIN32 /* Work around so Visual C++ 2005 will compile correctly with /O2 */
00053     strcpy(temp_filename, filename);
00054     hdf_status = Fid = GDopen(temp_filename,DFACC_READ);
00055   #else
00056     hdf_status = Fid = GDopen((char*)filename,DFACC_READ);
00057   #endif
00058   
00059   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00060     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_GDOPEN_FAILED);
00061 
00062   /* Determine MISR product file type */
00063   status = MtkFileTypeFid(Fid, filetype);
00064   MTK_ERR_COND_JUMP(status);
00065 
00066   hdf_status = GDclose(Fid);
00067   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00068     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_GDCLOSE_FAILED);
00069   Fid = FAIL;
00070 
00071   return MTK_SUCCESS;
00072 
00073 ERROR_HANDLE:
00074   if (Fid != FAIL) GDclose(Fid);
00075   return status_code;
00076 }

00083 MTKt_status MtkFileTypeFid(
00084   int32 Fid,               
00085   MTKt_FileType *filetype   )
00086 {
00087   MTKt_status status;
00088   MTKt_status status_code;
00089   intn hdf_status;
00090   char *lgid;
00091   char *fn_start;
00092   int num_grids;
00093   char **gridlist = NULL;
00094   int32 gridID;
00095   int32 projcode;
00096   int32 zonecode;
00097   int32 spherecode;
00098   float64 projparm[13];
00099   int32 sid;            /* HDF SD identifier (required by MtkFileLGID) */
00100   int32 HDFfid;         /* HDF file identifier (not used) */
00101   
00102   if (filetype == NULL)
00103     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_NULLPTR);
00104 
00105   /* It's possible for a file to have both conventional and stacked-block
00106      format in the same file but this is not used for MISR so only the
00107      first grid in the file is checked. */
00108 
00109   status = MtkFileToGridListFid(Fid,&num_grids,&gridlist);
00110   if (status != MTK_SUCCESS)
00111     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00112  
00113   hdf_status = gridID = GDattach(Fid,gridlist[0]);
00114   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00115     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_GDATTACH_FAILED);
00116 
00117   hdf_status = GDprojinfo(gridID,&projcode,&zonecode,&spherecode,projparm);
00118   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00119     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_GDPROJINFO_FAILED);
00120 
00121   hdf_status = GDdetach(gridID);
00122   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00123     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_GDDETACH_FAILED);
00124 
00125   MtkStringListFree(num_grids, &gridlist);
00126 
00127   if (projparm[11] == 0)
00128   {
00129     *filetype = MTK_CONVENTIONAL;
00130     return MTK_SUCCESS;
00131   }
00132 
00133   /* Determine type of stacked-block product */
00134 
00135   /* Get the HDF SD identifier. */
00136   hdf_status = EHidinfo(Fid, &HDFfid, &sid);
00137   if (hdf_status == FAIL)
00138     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_HDFEOS_EHIDINFO_FAILED);
00139 
00140   /* Get Local Granual ID */
00141   status = MtkFileLGIDFid(sid,&lgid);
00142   if (status != MTK_SUCCESS)
00143     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00144 
00145   fn_start = strstr(lgid, "MISR_AM1_");
00146   if (fn_start == NULL)
00147     MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_FAILURE);
00148 
00149   fn_start += 9; /* Skip MISR_AM1_ */
00150 
00151   /* Determine file type */
00152   if (strncmp(fn_start,"AGP",3) == 0)
00153     *filetype = MTK_AGP;
00154   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GP_GMP",6) == 0)
00155     *filetype = MTK_GP_GMP;
00156   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GRP_RCCM",8) == 0)
00157     *filetype = MTK_GRP_RCCM;
00158   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GRP_ELLIPSOID_GM",16) == 0)
00159     *filetype = MTK_GRP_ELLIPSOID_GM;
00160   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GRP_TERRAIN_GM",14) == 0)
00161     *filetype = MTK_GRP_TERRAIN_GM;
00162   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GRP_ELLIPSOID_LM",16) == 0)
00163     *filetype = MTK_GRP_ELLIPSOID_LM;
00164   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"GRP_TERRAIN_LM",14) == 0)
00165     *filetype = MTK_GRP_TERRAIN_LM;
00166   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"AS_AEROSOL",10) == 0)
00167     *filetype = MTK_AS_AEROSOL;
00168   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"AS_LAND",7) == 0)
00169     *filetype = MTK_AS_LAND;
00170   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"TC_ALBEDO",9) == 0)
00171     *filetype = MTK_TC_ALBEDO;
00172   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"TC_CLASSIFIERS",14) == 0)
00173     *filetype = MTK_TC_CLASSIFIERS;
00174   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"TC_STEREO",9) == 0)
00175     *filetype = MTK_TC_STEREO;
00176   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"PGRP_ELLIPSOID_GM",17) == 0)
00177     *filetype = MTK_GRP_ELLIPSOID_GM;
00178   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"PGRP_TERRAIN_GM",15) == 0)
00179     *filetype = MTK_GRP_TERRAIN_GM;
00180   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"PP",2) == 0)
00181     *filetype = MTK_PP;
00182   else if (strncmp(fn_start,"TC_CLOUD",8) == 0)
00183     *filetype = MTK_TC_CLOUD;
00184   else
00185     *filetype = MTK_UNKNOWN;
00186 
00187   free(lgid);
00188 
00189   return MTK_SUCCESS;
00190 
00191 ERROR_HANDLE:
00192   if (gridlist != NULL)
00193     MtkStringListFree(num_grids, &gridlist);
